<html>
  <problem>
    <title> CheckPoint: Period of Different Orbits </title>

<p>Satellite 1 revolves around a planet at the altitude equal to one-half the radius of the planet. The period of revolutions of satellite 1 is \(T_{1}\). What is the period of revolutions \(T_{2}\) of an identical satellite 2 that revolves around the same planet at the altitude equal to the radius of the planet?</p>

    <multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="yes" type="MultipleChoice">
      <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
        <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="true">
              \(T_{2}\) = \(T_{1} \sqrt{64/27}\)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">
              \(T_{2}\) = \(T_{1} \sqrt{16/9}\)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">
              \(T_{2}\) = \(T_{1} \sqrt{4/3}\)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">
              \(T_{2}\) = \(T_{1} \sqrt{3/2}\)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">
              \(T_{2}\) = \(T_{1} \sqrt{27/64}\)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">
              \(T_{2}\) = \(T_{1} \sqrt{9/16}\)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil7" correct="false">
              \(T_{2}\) = \(T_{1} \sqrt{3/4}\)          
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil8" correct="false">
              \(T_{2}\) = \(T_{1} \sqrt{2/3}\)          
        </choice>
      </choicegroup>
    </multiplechoiceresponse>
  </problem>
